parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended airbag deployment can cause injuries to occupants, distract the driver, and lead to accidents.
symptoms: without any apparent reason or crash

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure of Airbags to Deploy in a Crash
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as occupants may not receive the necessary protection.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake light switch can cause the vehicle to have no illumination for braking, which can lead to accidents or injuries to the driver and other road users.
symptoms: The brake lights do not function
the vehicle has no illumination for braking.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the instrument cluster can cause the driver to be unable to read important information such as the time and temperature, which can lead to inconvenience and potentially affect vehicle safety.
symptoms: The time and temperature sections of the instrument cluster lose lines or pixels
making it difficult or impossible to read the time and temperature.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A defective battery can cause acid to spill all over the engine, leading to an explosion, which can cause injuries or fatalities to the driver and other occupants.
symptoms: The vehicle explodes when attempting to start the engine
acid spills all over the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Corrosion-Induced Front Coil Spring Perch Failure
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the front coil spring perch can cause the coil spring to detach from the vehicle, leading to a loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The coil spring perch rusts or corrodes
causing the coil spring to detach from the vehicle
the front end of the vehicle collapses
the vehicle becomes unstable and difficult to control
the tire rubs against the fender
and the vehicle is prone to loss of control at high speeds.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the crankshaft position sensor can cause the engine to die without warning, leading to a loss of power and control, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: the engine will only turn but not ignite

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the catalytic converter can cause vibrations, rattling noises, and hard shifting in the transmission, which can lead to a loss of vehicle control and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: Rattling or vibrating noise from the catalytic converter

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission fluid can cause hard shifting, transmission problems, and premature wear on the transmission, which can lead to costly repairs and increased risk of accidents.
The failure of the digital instrument cluster can cause inaccurate temperature and time readings, and burned-out LEDs, which can lead to driver distraction and increased risk of accidents.
symptoms: burned-out LEDs in the speedometer area.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Tire tread separation and blowout can cause loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: Tread separation of more than a half of an inch

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Bent rims can cause tire failure, leading to loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially serious injuries or fatalities.
